node.text:
Thought we’d try something a little different with this recap video and hide a little surprise in the music🇺🇸😎

The past weekend up in the #pacificnorthwest have been amazing. Two shows. One weekend. And the first time we’ve flown the demo for Northwest Washington. 

Can anyone tell what our music choice was?

🎥: @codie.trimble l #F35DemoTeam
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Have you had the chance to go to one of our air shows yet? 

Whether you’re a die-hard aviation enthusiast or wanting to teach your family about the subject, air shows are a great way to have fun and educate yourself about the world of aviation.

Shout out to the Thoreson family for letting us follow you around @dekeslaytonairfest to make this video! 

Check out the link in our bio for our air show schedule and we hope to see you at one soon! ✈️🤟🏽
.
🎥: Staff Sergeant Thomas Barley 
.
.
. 
@aircombatcommand l @usairforce 
.
.
.

node.text:
Our mission is to recruit, engage and inspire the next generation of leaders. While flying at air shows is amazing, the people and communities we meet with make it all worth it.

Were looking foward to meeting you all this weekend, May 22-23, at the Atlanta Air Show, so dont hesitate to come up to us and say hi! 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
During the time between air shows, we like to take it as a time to reflect and look back. To see how we can use the past to make the future better.

2020 was an insane year, for a lot of different reasons, and it made our first year as an @aircombatcommand Demo Team one to remember.

Who knows what 2021 will bring, but we're hoping that at the very least, it means more air shows and more chances to showcase this team to the world. 

If you told us two years ago where we'd be now, we wouldn't have believed you. Thanks for all of your support, and thanks for 200K.

We're proud to call ourselves your @usairforce F-35A Lightning II Demonstration Team.

📹: @codie.trimble

node.text:
Like something out of the movies 🎞️🍿⁣
⁣
Coming to an airshow is a special experience for all of us, and to be able to perform for people around the world is a privilege and an honor.⁣
⁣
With three out of four @usairforce @aircombatcommand jet demo teams in one place, we had a blast in #WashingtonState. ⁣
⁣
We'll see you soon Canada for @airshowlondon 🇨🇦.⁣
⁣
📹: @kip_em_flying l #F35DemoTeam⁣
.⁣

Ever Upwards ☝️
⁣
With over 2,600 cars in attendance, being able to perform for the @newyorkairshow massive drive-in audience was definitely one of the highlights of this season.⁣
⁣
We're constantly amazed at the love and passion for flight that we see at every show.⁣
⁣
If you missed us, here's a small look at our airshow experience.⁣
⁣
🎥: Staff Sgt Tompkins l #F35DemoTeam⁣

A show like never before 😤⁣
⁣
While we've had a turbulent 2020 show season, we've made the shows we go to count. ⁣
⁣
With almost every single @usairforce demo team there, and some historic vapes, the #OCAirshow was one for the highlight reel.⁣
⁣
Coming up: the @newyorkairshow.⁣
⁣
🎥: SSgt Tompkins l #F35DemoTeam⁣

node.text:
Watch the Northern Skies 

We've arrived in #Alaska for this weekend's Arctic Lightning air show at @eielsonafb !!

We had an awesome practice day yesterday and are ready to show off what this jet is capable of!

A huge shout-out to the 354th Fighter Wing for allowing us to use their aircraft!

#DYK? The 354th Fighter Wing in Alaska will be home to two combat-ready F-35 squadrons, and will be the second operational F35 Wing in the @usairforce, following the @388fw? 

#F35DemoTeam l #ReadyAF 

📸: Capt Kip Sumner

node.text:
No music, just jet noise.🇺🇸

With a maximum altitude of 50,000 feet and a max speed of about 1,200mph, the F-35 can reach its cruising altitude in less than a minute. 

While we don’t fly that high during our demonstration profile, we do showcase the jets quick-climbing capabilities in a variety of maneuvers. 

Any questions about this beast? Shoot us a message @f35demoteam.

node.text:
#didyouknow Major Wolfe flies the F-35A at elevations as low as 300’ above ground level during her demonstration profile.

Flying these maneuvers requires pinpoint precision and attention to detail to ensure safe flying...and an awesome show for all to see.🙌🏼

Here’s some of our faves from a recent low-level flight over Central Washington, while enroute to an air show in the #pnw.

Thanks to @dwhonan for catching these shots for us📸😎
